{"title_page": "Mladen Vasilev", "text_new": "{{short description|Bulgarian footballer and coach}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Mladen Vasilev\n|image          = \u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432 00511.jpg\n|image_size     = 150\n|caption        = Mladen Vasilev in present days.\n|fullname       = Mladen Aleksandrov Vasilev\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1947|7|29}}\n|birth_place    = [[Slivnitsa]], [[Bulgaria]]\n|height         = \n|position       = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]] / [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|youthyears1    = \n|youthclubs1    = \n|years1         = 1965\u20131968\n|clubs1         = [[FC Slivnishki Geroy|Slivnishki Geroy]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 1968\u20131969\n|clubs2         = [[PFC Slavia Sofia|Slavia Sofia]]\n|caps2          = 12\n|goals2         = 2\n|years3         = 1969\u20131977\n|clubs3         = [[PFC Akademik Sofia|Akademik Sofia]]\n|caps3          = 209\n|goals3         = 68\n|totalcaps      = \n|totalgoals     = \n|nationalyears1 = 1974\u20131975\n|nationalteam1  = [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 4\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Mladen \"Maho\" Aleksandrov Vasilev''' ({{lang-bg|\u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d A\u043be\u043aca\u043d\u0434po\u0432 \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432}}; born 29 July 1947 in [[Slivnitsa]]) is a former [[Bulgaria]]n [[association football|football]] player, and later [[Coach (sport)|coach]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Slivnitsa]], Vasilev started his career with local side [[FC Slivnishki Geroy|Slivnishki Geroy]]. Later he played for [[PFC Slavia Sofia]] (1968\u20131969), and [[PFC Akademik Sofia|Akademik Sofia]] (1969\u20131977, 209 times and 68 [[Goal (sport)|goals]]).\n\nHe played for [[Bulgaria national football team]], including the [[1974 FIFA World Cup]] in [[West Germany]].\n\n==External links==\n* [http://people.slivnitsa.com/%D0%BC%D0%BB%D0%B0%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%B2 Mladen Vasilev in Slivnitsa.com]\n* {{NFT player|pid=29859}}\n\n{{Bulgaria Squad 1974 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vasilev, Mladen}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian footballers]]\n[[Category:1974 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Bulgaria international footballers]]\n[[Category:Akademik Sofia players]]\n[[Category:PFC Slavia Sofia players]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n{{Bulgaria-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Mladen Vasilev\n|image          = \u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432 00511.jpg\n|image_size     = 150\n|caption        = Mladen Vasilev in present days.\n|fullname       = Mladen Aleksandrov Vasilev\n|birth_date     = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1947|7|29}}\n|birth_place    = [[Slivnitsa]], [[Bulgaria]]\n|height         = \n|position       = [[Midfielder#Winger|Winger]] / [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|youthyears1    = \n|youthclubs1    = \n|years1         = 1965\u20131968\n|clubs1         = [[FC Slivnishki Geroy|Slivnishki Geroy]]\n|caps1          = \n|goals1         = \n|years2         = 1968\u20131969\n|clubs2         = [[PFC Slavia Sofia|Slavia Sofia]]\n|caps2          = 12\n|goals2         = 2\n|years3         = 1969\u20131977\n|clubs3         = [[PFC Akademik Sofia|Akademik Sofia]]\n|caps3          = 209\n|goals3         = 68\n|totalcaps      = \n|totalgoals     = \n|nationalyears1 = 1974\u20131975\n|nationalteam1  = [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 4\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Mladen \"Maho\" Aleksandrov Vasilev''' ({{lang-bg|\u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043d A\u043be\u043aca\u043d\u0434po\u0432 \u0412\u0430\u0441\u0438\u043b\u0435\u0432}}; born 29 July 1947 in [[Slivnitsa]]) is a former [[Bulgaria]]n [[association football|football]] player, and later [[Coach (sport)|coach]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Slivnitsa]], Vasilev started his career with local side [[FC Slivnishki Geroy|Slivnishki Geroy]]. Later he played for [[PFC Slavia Sofia]] (1968\u20131969), and [[PFC Akademik Sofia|Akademik Sofia]] (1969\u20131977, 209 times and 68 [[Goal (sport)|goals]]).\n\nHe played for [[Bulgaria national football team]], including the [[1974 FIFA World Cup]] in [[West Germany]].\n\n==External links==\n* [http://people.slivnitsa.com/%D0%BC%D0%BB%D0%B0%D0%B4%D0%B5%D0%BD-%D0%B2%D0%B0%D1%81%D0%B8%D0%BB%D0%B5%D0%B2 Mladen Vasilev in Slivnitsa.com]\n* {{NFT player|pid=29859}}\n\n{{Bulgaria Squad 1974 World Cup}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vasilev, Mladen}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian footballers]]\n[[Category:1974 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:Bulgaria international footballers]]\n[[Category:Akademik Sofia players]]\n[[Category:PFC Slavia Sofia players]]\n[[Category:First Professional Football League (Bulgaria) players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n{{Bulgaria-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lepricavark", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:added short description", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mladen_Vasilev"}
