tive = 1985\u2013present\n| module       = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent\n | hangul      = {{linktext|\ubc15|\uc601|\uaddc}}\n | hanja       = {{linktext|\u6734|\u69ae|\u594e}}\n | rr          = Bak Yeong-gyu\n | mr          = Pak Y\u014fngkyu\n }}\n}}\n'''Park Yeong-gyu''' (born 28 October 1953) is a [[South Korea]]n actor. He is best known for his roles in ''[[Attack the Gas Station]]'', in which he plays the owner of the titular gas station, and ''[[Break Out (film)|Break Out]]'', in which he plays a corrupt politician.\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=wikitable style=\"width:600px;\"\n! width=30| Year \n! Title \n! Role\n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1985 || ''College Story'' || \n|-\n| ''The Parting'' || \n|-\n| 1987 || ''Lethe's Love Song'' || \n|-\n| rowspan=2 | 1988 || ''Tip'' || Jang-ho \n|-\n| ''Love's Scribble'' || Gil-soo\n|-\n| rowspan=4 | 1989 || ''Rainbow over Seoul'' || President Pyo\n|-\n| ''Ae-ran'' || Yoshimura\n|-\n| ''Gigolo in Shinsa-dong'' || Gigolo Dosa\n|-\n| ''Flesh Trade'' || \n|-\n| 1991 || ''Tomorrow's Rain'' || \n|-\n| 1992 || ''The Emperor of Romance'' || <!-- Joogeun Noh --> Master Noh\n|-\n| 1995 || ''No Emergency Exit'' || Rock cafe employee\n|-\n| 1999 || ''[[Attack the Gas Station]]'' || Gas station owner \n|-\n| 2001 || ''The Humanist'' || Father\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2002 || ''[[A.F.R.I.K.A.]]'' || Gas station owner\n|-\n| ''[[Break Out (film)|Break Out]]'' || Park Yeong-gab \n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2003 || ''Season in the Sun'' || Monk Woo-nam \n|-\n| ''Oh! Brothers'' || President Park ([[cameo appearance|cameo]])\n|-\n| ''[[Happy Ero Christmas]]'' || Bang Seok-doo\n|-\n| rowspan=3 | 2004 || ''Dance with Solitude'' || Bae Jung-beom\n|-\n| ''[[Ghost House (film)|Ghost House]]'' || Man crawling out of TV set ([[cameo appearance|cameo]])\n|-\n| ''Flower Shop'' ([[short film]]) || \n|-\n| 2010 || ''[[Attack the Gas Station 2]]'' || Gas station owner<ref>{{cite web|last=Song|first=Woong-ki|title=Director Kim Sang-jin runs