{"title_page": "Kim Sang-jin (film director)", "text_new": "{{Korean name|Kim}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Kim Sang-jin\n| image        =\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1967|8|9}}\n| birth_place  = [[South Korea]]\n| occupation   = [[Film director]], [[screenwriter]], [[film producer|producer]]\n| years_active = 1989-present\n| spouse       = \n| education    = [[Hanyang University]] - Theater and Film\n| module       = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent|\n| hangul       = {{linktext|\uae40|\uc0c1|\uc9c4}}\n| hanja        = {{linktext|\u91d1|\u76f8|\u8fb0}}\n| rr           = Gim Sang-jin\n| mr           = Kim Sangchin\n}}}}\n'''Kim Sang-jin''' (born August 9, 1967) is a [[South Korea]]n [[film director]], [[screenwriter]] and [[film producer|producer]].<ref>{{cite web|title=KIM Sang-jin|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/films/index/peopleView.jsp?peopleCd=10004438|website=Korean Film Biz Zone|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> He directed the hit comedies ''[[Attack the Gas Station]]'' (1999), ''[[Kick the Moon]]'' (2001) and ''[[Jail Breakers]]'' (2002).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Gab-sik|title=Film Review - ''The Moonlit Night in Shilla''|url=http://english.donga.com/srv/service.php3?bicode=130000&biid=2001061918318|website=[[The Dong-a Ilbo]]|accessdate=15 July 2015|date=18 June 2001}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Sang-eon|title=Director refuses to get serious|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2482249|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=15 July 2015|date=19 October 2004}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Press Conference - ''Attack The Gas Station 2''|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2009121817542230861|website=10Asia|accessdate=15 July 2015|date=18 December 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Song|first1=Woong-ki|title=Director Kim Sang-jin runs out of gas|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20100114000045|website=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=15 July 2015|dat